data.name: XModuleUIConfigurationManager
desc: specifies specific functions of a module based user interface configuration manager interface.
A module user interface configuration manager supports, unlike a document based ui configuration manager, two layers of configuration settings data:

methods.name: getDefaultSettings
desc: retrieves the settings from the default layer of the user interface configuration manager if it has a default layer.

methods.name: isDefaultSettings
desc: determine if the settings of a user interface element is part of the default layer of the user interface configuration manager.
